VIRTUAL ENVIRONMENT IN LINUX UBANTU(20.04) 

1.create virutual environment
--> virtualenv <env-name>

2.activate virtual environment
--> source <env-name>/bin/activate

3.deactivate env
--> deactivate

4.create requirements.txt file
--> pip3 freeze > requirements.txt

5.auto install requirement.txt in another environment
-->pip3 install -r requirements.txt

